# Working with data

Prontotype provides a simple but powerful set of tools for including and working with data in your prototypes.

It's possible to parse and use data in [YAML, JSON, XML, CSV and Markdown]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('data-formats') }}) formats. You can either use [local data files]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('data-local') }}) or retrieve data from [external sources]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('data-external') }}) via HTTP requests.

Prontotype also provides a simple way of [auto-generating 'fake' data]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('data-fake') }}) to help populate your prototype quickly and easily.

Lastly, all data files are also parsed through the [Twig template parser]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('templating-twig') }}) so you can use loops, logic, includes and so on within them, if required. 

## Accessing data within your templates

There are a number of methods available to access your data from you templates. Full details of these are covered in the [data templating reference]({{ pt.pages.getUrlById('template-ref-data') }}).

